            <title>[JCR-338] Query Builder and jcr:deref problem. Can&apos;t add predicate after jcr:deref</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-338</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>Cannot add a predicate (like [@property = &amp;#39;value&amp;#39;] after a jcr:deref function.&lt;br/&gt;
The query builder throws an &amp;quot;InvalidQueryException: Unsupported location for jcr:deref()&amp;quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
So for example, the query :&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
//element(*,nt:category)[@member]/jcr:deref(@member, &amp;#39;*&amp;#39;)[@property=&amp;#39;value&amp;#39;] &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
is invalid and it should be valid.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
